  "text": "The similar prognosis of diabetics and non-diabetics after normal SPECT is in accordance with prior studies [CITATION_1] . However, the event rate after normal SPECT, although initially similar, is reported to increase after 2 years of follow-up and thus a shorter warranty period of SPECT may apply in diabetic patients [CITATION_2] . One must be cautious about using our data to predict the long-term prognosis of a normal SPECT in diabetic patients.",
